ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Math 500 is a thorough introduction to commutative algebra, building the basics for algebraic geometry. I would recommend this course to other students, as it was an enjoyable course that also contributed significantly to my academic growth.
We covered all of Atiyah-MacDonald and achieved a good understanding of basic commutative algebra.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course certainly deepened my understanding of commutative algebra as well as of algebra in general. The extent to which this will be useful for my research remains to be seen, but I'm sure the utility will be nonzero.
